text: Gorny Klyuch () is a rural locality (a village) in Bakhmutsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 113 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 18 km from Yermolayevo, 6 km from Bakhmut. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Gorny Klyuch
